	<owl:Class rdf:about="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdmplus#BibliographicResource">
		<rdfs:comment>Root of the taxonomy of the non-information bibliographic resources provided by the Publication Office of the European Union (OP). These things of interest are identified by HTTP URIs.</rdfs:comment>
		<rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdmplus#OpResource"/>
	</owl:Class>
	<owl:Class rdf:about="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdmplus#BibliographicResourceExpression">
		<rdfs:comment>BibliographicResourceExpression is a class acting as collector of metadata (properties) describing a Bibliographic Resource at Expression level of the IFLA model. Namely it collects the properties describing a Bibliographic Resource able to identify any different version over the time or across languages (Expression aspect of a Bibliographic Resource).</rdfs:comment>
	</owl:Class>
	<owl:Class rdf:about="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdmplus#BibliographicResourceItem">
		<rdfs:comment>BibliographicResourceItem is the class of the single copies (items in IFLA terms) of a Bibliographic Resource (Item aspect of a Bibliographic Resource).</rdfs:comment>
	</owl:Class>
	<owl:Class rdf:about="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdmplus#BibliographicResourceManifestation">
		<rdfs:comment>BibliographicResourceManifestation is a class acting as collector of metadata (properties) describing a Bibliographic Resource at Manifestation level of the IFLA model. Namely it collects the properties describing a Bibliographic Resource able to identify any different realisation (paper format, digital format, etc) of an Expression (Manifestation aspect of a Bibliographic Resource).</rdfs:comment>
	</owl:Class>
	<owl:Class rdf:about="http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/cdmplus#BibliographicResourceWork">
		<rdfs:comment>BibliographicResourceWork is a class acting as collector of metadata (properties) describing a Bibliographic Resource at Work level of the IFLA model. Namely it collects the properties describing a Bibliographic Resource as a disctinct intellectual creation (Work aspect of a Bibliographic Resource).</rdfs:comment>
	</owl:Class>
